BXzeal package

A perverse way to get XeTeX logo.

* INSTALL

  You need the Latin Modern Fonts (Type1) installed.

  - bxzeal.sty ->      $TEXMF/tex/latex/BXzeal
  - bxzeal.map ->      $TEXMF/fonts/map/dvips/BXzeal
  - zlmr-r-l7c.tfm ->  $TEXMF/fonts/tfm/public/BXzeal
  - zr-l7c.enc ->      $TEXMF/fonts/enc/dvips/BXzeal

  Register bxzeal.map with your updmap.
  (TeX Live: updmap(-sys) --enable Map=bxzeal.map)
  (W32TeX: updmap --add bxzeal.map)

* USAGE

  Load the package in usual way.

    \usepackage{bxzeal}

  If you specify the option dvipdfmx, this package will work in using
  dvipdfmx, even if you don't register the map file with updmap.

    \Usepackage[dvipdfmx]{bxzeal}

  The package provides only two commands, namely \XeTeX and \XeLaTeX,
  whose meaning will be obvious!

